# =============================================================================
# Logs and Temporary Files
# =============================================================================
*.log
*.log.*
logs/
log/

# =============================================================================
# Project-Specific Excludes
# =============================================================================
# Large TCGA data files
*.xml
gdc_manifest*.txt
*_manifest.txt

# SCADEN training outputs
scaden_training.log
*/SCADEN_Output/**

# CIBERSORTx files (keep small signature matrices, exclude large results)
CIBERSORTx_Results_*.txt
CIBERSORTx_Adjusted_*.txt
*_Window*.txt

# Specific large directories to exclude entirely
data/raw/
data/processed/*.h5ad
TCGAdata/rna/
TCGAdata/xml/

# =============================================================================
# Files to KEEP (Override above patterns)
# =============================================================================
# Important small configuration and documentation files
!README.md
!*.md
!requirements.txt
!setup.py
!pyproject.toml
!environment.yml

# Keep small summary/metadata files
!*_summary.csv
!*_metadata.csv
!*_config.csv
!*_parameters.csv

# Keep signature matrices and gene lists
!*signature*.txt
!*markers*.txt
!*genes*.txt
!NK_*.txt

# Keep small figures if needed (uncomment if you want to track some plots)
# !summary_plots/*.png
# !key_figures/*.pdf

# Keep CIBERSORTx signature files
!*signature_matrix*.tsv
!*signature_matrix*.txt
!NK_reference_matrix*.txt

# =============================================================================
# Important Notes
# =============================================================================
# This .gitignore excludes:
# 1. Large data files (.h5ad, .tsv, .xml, etc.)
# 2. Analysis outputs (plots, results directories)
# 3. Temporary and cache files
# 4. System and IDE files
# 
# It preserves:
# 1. Python scripts and notebooks (code)
# 2. Documentation files (.md)
# 3. Small configuration files
# 4. Gene signature files and markers
# 5. Small summary CSV files
#
# Remember to:
# - Review before first commit
# - Add large files to Git LFS if needed
# - Update this file as project evolves 